CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 4, 1959, p. A3, reads: "Platform Guests - Seated on the platform ground-breaking ceremonies, are outstanding civic, county and city officials, including Mrs. R. L. Vann and Mrs. W. W. Stanton, widows of former Loendi presidents. Also in picture are Mrs. Mary MacEnheimer, Councilman Paul F. Jones, and W. A. Harris, Sr., chairman of the event. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Paul F. Jones wearing pinstriped suit, and William "Woogie" Harris facing away with hand on railing small pavilion with bunting, with Jessie Vann, Mrs. W. W. Stanton, and Mary McEnheimer seated inside, for groundbreaking ceremony of Loendi Club on Ledlie Street
